The paper deals with resource allocation and trajectory design for secure communication systems using UAVs. This involves optimization of communication/jamming subcarrier allocation policy and the trajectory of UAVs, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also takes into account constraints on the minimum safety distance among multiple UAVs and the existence of no-fly zones, which are related to control systems (cs.SY). The presence of eavesdroppers and the need for secure communication suggests the paper may also belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of optimization algorithms to obtain a suboptimal solution suggests the paper may also belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
